::jsonb, '[{"title":"Civil Engineer_Contracts, Billing & Budgeting | Quantity Surveyor | Estimation & Costing","company":"Imported from resume CSV","description":"Assistant Cost Manager | Lambsrock Consulting (I) Pvt. Ltd. | | 2023-Present || Senior Billing Engineer | Shapoorji Pallonji & Co. Pvt. Ltd. | | 2022-2023 || Senior Engineer (Billing & Contracts) | Peritus Realty Solutions | | 2018-2022 || Billing Engineer | Marvel Realtors & Developers Limited | | 2015-2018 || Key Responsibilities | Billing & Estimation Engineer | Lashkaria Group | | 2011-2015 |  Contract & Bill Management: o Review contractor-submitted measurements as per the completion certificate issued by the project in-charge and coordinate with on-site teams to ensure accurate and timely processing of contractor invoices, in compliance with contractual deadlines. o Monitor theoretical consumption of steel, cement, and other materials provided to the contractor at no cost, and initiate cost recovery for instances of excess usage or wastage. o Certify contractor/subcontractor bills for civil and MEP works, ensuring compliance with tender rates. o Process vendor/subcontractor invoices, including joint measurement sheet verification. o Invite quotations from vendors, conduct rate analysis, and negotiate competitive rates to align with market benchmarks and project budgets. o Issue the work order to the contractor in accordance with the Scope of Work, Bill of Quantities (BOQ), and other agreed-upon contractual terms. o Initiate change orders and amendments to tender packages based on GFC drawings and site requirements.  Cost Control & Reconciliation: o Conduct rate analysis for extra/non-scheduled items and negotiate quotations with vendors. o Reconcile RA Bills to resolve payment disputes (e.g., retention amount releases). o Track material consumption (steel, cement, concrete, AAC blocks) and recover costs for excess usage/wastage.  Documentation & Compliance: o Prepare detailed reconciliation statements for materials, billed-to-client quantities, and subcontractor payments. o Review tender vs. GFC drawing variations and prepare deviation statements for reimbursement. o Ensure recovery of rework/faulty work costs from contractors as per site recommendations. 2 o Prepare a detailed cost recovery statement for materials supplied at no cost, analyzing theoretical vs. actual consumption to claim reimbursement for excess usage or wastage, in compliance with contractual terms. o Prepare a detailed recovery statement for advance payments, adhoc disbursements, and retention amounts, ensuring alignment with contractual terms and reconciliation of outstanding balances. o Prepare the contractor payment certificate by consolidating cumulative work progress and financial reconciliations from prior and current Running Account (RA) bills, ensuring alignment with contractual obligations and interim valuation reports.  Value Engineering & Reporting: o Analyze alternative methods/materials to reduce costs without compromising safety or quality. o Prepare comparative statements for vendor quotations and finalize cost-effective options. o Generate budget variance reports and track unbilled/work-in-progress quantities."}]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'F:\Resume All 1\Resume PDF\Doephode C.B..pdf', 'Name: Chandrakant B. Doephode

