ity and ease of assembly. Page 2 of 4  I organize, track, and maintain project data systematically, ensuring every detail — from initial design iterations to final revisions — is documented. This includes managing version control, adhering to client-specific document protocols, and preparing records for handover or external audit compliance. WSP Consultants RCD Technician – Structures ||  As an RCD Technician, I ensure that every aspect of the design brief is thoroughly reviewed from a Health & Safety | July | 2016-2024 | (H&S) perspective. I maintain a dedicated H&S register to document and track relevant safety considerations within the project scope. I actively support Desktop Audit checks during internal project audits within the structures team and contribute to estimation processes and cost-to-complete assessments for previous RCD projects.  I assist the Team Lead with addressing day-to-day project queries from UK project managers, site teams, and clients, ensuring quick and effective resolutions to avoid delays. I support the creation and refinement of project templates when needed and ensure smooth, effective communication with UK project leads and other key stakeholders. I manage and maintain comprehensive project records, covering planning, setup, safety in design, H&S, communication, document management, change management, reviews, issues, project closure, and feedback — all crucial for external audits.  I oversee delegated tasks to ensure deadlines are met, while proactively highlighting any resourcing challenges to the RCD Manager and team leads. I foster strong working relationships within the team, promoting resource sharing, collaboration, and mutual support. I continuously seek opportunities for self-improvement and skill development to enhance my technical capabilities. I align the project team to ensure timely delivery of project packages and analyze congested areas, providing 3D visual representations to support design clarity and decision-making. I am committed to driving operational excellence, ensuring projects meet safety, quality, and timeline objectives while fostering a collaborative, high-performing team environment. Ansal Housing Construction Ltd. Assistant Architect ||  I took charge of the architectural planning and design for diverse residential and commercial developments, | Oct | 2011-2016 | ensuring the layouts were functional, aesthetically appealing, and aligned with the client’s vision. My work involved balancing creative design solutions with practical considerations like site constraints, budget limitations, and regulatory requirements.  I utilized industry-standard software to create detailed 2D and 3D architectural drawings. This included floor plans, elevations, sections, and realistic visualizations to help clients and stakeholders envision the final structure. I ensured these designs met technical requirements while maintaining the intended architectural style.  I took an active role on-site to oversee construction progress. I ensured that the build matched the approved designs and adhered to safety protocols, local building codes, and municipal guidelines. This involved collaborating with contractors, engineers, and site managers to resolve any issues that emerged during construction.  I contributed to large-scale, multi-city projects, each with its own unique design challenges and requirements. My involvement ranged from conceptual design stages to final site supervision, ensuring quality and consistency across all locations.  Notable Projects: Ansal Town (Amritsar, Ajmer, Meerut, Ghaziabad, Karnal). SWBI Architects Pvt. Ltd. Assistant Architect ||  Designed layouts for housing and commercial properties. | Oct | 2010-2011 |  Trained in Google SketchUp for conceptual designs. Page 3 of 4  Worked closely with stakeholders to deliver on client expectation Uppal Housing Pvt. Ltd. Assistant Architect ||  Managed the design and drafting of residential layouts and interiors.